docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:14:| A-110 | 008F creates the narrow §28 security-package parent with `poa_required_flag=true` and keeps SH-4, CDSL, blank-cheque, and cancelled-cheque requirement flags false/pending until their named owners refresh those facts. Package status and `security_ready_flag` remain pending/false even after PoA activation. | The selected slice explicitly forbids implementing SH-4, CDSL, cheque, custody, or readiness outcomes, while §17.1 requires non-null package flags. Treating unimplemented instruments as required, complete, or ready would invent applicability/readiness truth. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §28.1-§28.6; `docs/source/data-model.md` §17.1; `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M06-FR-006-012/M06-FR-019; `docs/slices/008F-power-of-attorney-workflow.md` | 008F and later 008H/008I/008J/008K security-package owners | High | Yes | 2026-07-14 | Later instrument owners must refresh only their governed flags/outcomes and preserve PoA history. No partial package may claim disbursement readiness. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:18:| A-106 | Renderer contract `legal-renderer-v1` is current only when its immutable provenance snapshots match both the retained generated `document_id` and its SHA-256 metadata. Pre-contract or mismatched rows remain listable as `legacy_unverified`, conflict on exact replay, and are excluded from checklist/stamp/notary current-output selectors. 008B4 provides no automatic remediation path: a future governed successor flow must preserve any executed, verified, checklist-linked, stamped, or notarised history. | Source requires template/file history and genuine Word/PDF generation but does not name a renderer-contract version, legacy status vocabulary, or remediation operation. A versioned all-or-none binding is the smallest non-destructive mechanism that prevents metadata flags/extensions from upgrading old bytes; refusing remediation avoids inventing overwrite authority. | `docs/source/codebase-design.md` §§14.1/26.1-26.3/27.1/36.1-36.2/42.2; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §§6-8/26.4-26.5; `docs/source/data-model.md` §§16.1-16.3/34; `docs/source/functional-spec.md` §15.1/M06-FR-013/M06-FR-015; architecture review `2026-07-14_124337_architecture_review` | 008B4 and later checklist/stamp/notary/remediation owners | High | Yes | 2026-07-14 | Governance may version a future renderer contract or authorize a successor/remediation endpoint; never backfill provenance from extension, MIME type, flags, prefix, or unchecked legacy bytes, and never mutate retained provenance. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:23:| A-101 | The implemented M05 terminal path does not yet own numeric interest rate, repayment date, penal rate, charges policy, or a distinct dispute-resolution clause; therefore a source-complete 13-field Term Sheet must remain configuration-blocked when an approved template declares those missing fields. A test that directly inserts a fully populated `SanctionDecision` proves renderer capability only, not an end-to-end M05-to-M06 workflow. | A-079 deliberately retained honest null/empty sanction terms because no approved frozen source supplies them. 008B correctly refuses missing required merge facts, but its positive tracer bypasses the real terminal writer and cannot establish M06-FR-013 production readiness. Inventing rates, dates, fees, or legal clauses would violate DECISION_POLICY §1.3. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` §15.1 and M06-FR-013; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §§25.8/26.4; Epic 008 digest V10 p.17 §4.9; A-079; architecture review `2026-07-14_093142_architecture_review` | 008B3 and a future source-governed sanction-term/configuration owner | High | Yes | 2026-07-14 | 008B3 must label the real-path blocker and renderer fixture honestly. When governance identifies the authoritative rate/repayment/fee/clause owners and approval semantics, freeze those facts before terminal decision and add a real public-workflow tracer; never derive them from current mutable policy or test-only rows. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:24:| A-100 | Exact loan-document replay is identified by application, retained immutable template row, and output format and returns the first retained result without new bytes or evidence. Generated legal-package rows start as category `legal`, party required `borrower`, execution `pending`, and verification `pending`. Retained template bodies use exact `{{ field_name }}` placeholders for every declared merge field. The initial Term Sheet merge vocabulary is `borrower_name`, `nominee_name`, `shares_held`, `facility`, `loan_amount`, `loan_purpose`, `interest_rate`, `interest_tenure`, `repayment_date`, `penal_interest_rate`, `charges_and_fees`, `security`, and `dispute_resolution`; optional `witness_name` is supported for agreement templates. Nominee, verified witness, and shareholding values come only from the approval-owned frozen review package, never mutable live rows. Until a distinct configured clause store exists, `dispute_resolution` resolves only from explicitly persisted sanctioned `conditions_precedent` text and is missing/blocked when that text is absent; generation never supplies clause wording. | API §26.4 fixes request/response fields but not replay behavior, category/party defaults, initial state literals, template placeholder syntax, merge-field identifiers, or a separate persisted dispute-clause field. These conservative values preserve the §16.3 lifecycle, require an attributable frozen value for every merge, consume retained approved template bytes, and retain one unambiguous evidence set without inventing later execution/checklist completion or legal wording. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §26.4-§26.5; `docs/source/data-model.md` §16.3; `docs/source/functional-spec.md` §15.1; Epic 008 digest V10 p.17 §4.9; `docs/slices/008B-document-generation-shell.md` | 008B and later execution/checklist/template-governance slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-14 | If governance adds a dedicated configured dispute-resolution clause or defines regeneration/reason semantics, party/category configuration, placeholder syntax, or different merge identifiers, version future templates and generation identities; never rewrite retained generated documents. |
